  "title": "Resident Technical Officer(C&S RTO) - Changi",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monitor work progress, site safety, and quality control, ensuring proper documentation and reporting.</li>\n  <li>Verify materials, inspect works, and raise discrepancies to the supervising team.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with contractors, consultants, authorities, and stakeholders to resolve site issues.</li>\n  <li>Attend site meetings and maintain accurate records of progress, inspections, and variations.</li>\n  <li>Assist in reviewing method statements and ensuring proper site execution.</li>\n  <li>Ensure works comply with environmental, health, and safety regulations.</li>\n  <li>Assist in preparing site instructions, defect lists, and submission forms</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma / Degree in Civil/Structural Engineering</li>\n  <li>On site in supervision of works similar in nature to major construction works in deep excavation works.</li>\n  <li>Registered Resident Technical Officer (RTO) with at least 3 years of relevant experience.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
